				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I guess I would have to look at the problem you are trying to resolve and then ask what is the best solution to the problem.
<br />

<br />
The fisrt problem is farming MObs to the point that nobody can get the drop on there own. 
<br />

<br />
The second problem is pricing on the item that is being farmed.
<br />

<br />
Making it no drop is a solution to the problem but it would exclude anyone that does not belong to a guild/group that can farm the MOb from ever getting the item.  It would also prevent us from passing down that gear to younger rangers in our guilds when we have outgrown the drop, so guilds would have to constantly farm the items for newer/younger members.  Basically, we would just move the farming to different people in this case.  If this is the case, then I would ahve to say no to making it no drop.
<br />

<br />
Plat selling is driving up the pricing, so putting an end to this would probably be the best solution, but I think we all know that SOE is not going to do this.
<br />

<br />
Without a lot of programming on SOE's part, I don't really see a good solution to this.  But a really nice solution would be a greed monster <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" /> If you loot certain items more than a certain number of times an unkillable greed monster pops, takes all your gear and coin, and camps your corpse for 7 days.<br />_________________<br />Forest Stalker of the 65th season 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=988276" target="_blank" class="postlink">Rexcillius Ridgerunner</a>
