				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I had to vote no. I agree with the point the poster made about many players who are unguilded not having any access to certain items at all without the bazaar. What I really think needs to be done is the availability of platinum in the game needs to be reduced back to the level it was at in the old days when you scrimped and saved every copper just to keep from starving to death. There is way too much money in the game and too many mobs with big (for their level) loot drops that even a low level player can farm. What we need is for Sony to nerf a lot of loot drops in the game to reduce the amount of plat entering the game and add a lot more plat sinks as roadblocks to advancement to pull a lot of the excess cash out. That will kill the plat sellers and drop prices once and for all.<br />_________________<br />If you were me, and I were you, would we still be friends??</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
